-- Japan, China Agree to Communicate to Avoid Sea Confrontations, Kyodo Says
-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 2010-10-11T06:47:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/japan-china-agree-to-communicate-to-avoid-sea-confrontations-kyodo-says.html
(Corrects source of report to Jiji Press.)  Japanese Defense Minister Toshimi
Kitazawa and Chinese counterpart Liang Guanglie agreed to
promptly establish a maritime communications system between the
two countries to avoid incidents at sea, Jiji Press reported.
Meeting in Hanoi, they also agreed on the need to develop a
mutually beneficial strategic relationship, Jiji said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kana Nishizawa in Tokyo at 
